PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
TAGS: #list
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly limit.

STRUCTURE: Dashboard
MARKER: dashboard
INTENT: the main screen showing all categories and their balances
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a section for each budget category showing its name, balance, and limit, and a summary at the bottom with total income and expenses.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the "Add Category" button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and limit. The new category is added to the list and displayed on the dashboard.

WHEN: Update Category Balance
MARKER: update_category_balance
INTENT: user updates the balance of a category
TAGS: #card, #form, #user
---
When the user taps the "Edit" button on a category card, a form appears. The user updates the balance and saves the changes. The updated balance is reflected on the card and the summary.

ASSERT: Category Limits
MARKER: category_limits
INTENT: ensure categories do not exceed their limits
---
A category's balance cannot exceed its monthly limit. If a category's balance exceeds its limit, a warning is shown.

SURFACE: Category Card
MARKER: category_card
INTENT: labels and styles for category cards
TAGS: #card
---
The category card shows the category name, current balance, and limit. The card has a strikethrough style if the balance exceeds the limit.